rComments: Difficult to get good grades in this class. I took it as an elective. The exams are usually long answers and she looks for specific answers or she wont give you a good grade. She's rather aggressive in her emails and corrections for whatever reason. She is passionate but this was a heavy and stressful class for me. Would not take again

The whole class is setup in a very weird way, nothing is chronologically correct, its split in five ways; societies, economics, wtv. I learned more in my grade 11th class thats all im gonna say. If you want to learn about the main events dont take this class as she talked about potatoes for 40 minutes and the french revolution for 8 minutes.
Great prof!

C'est une bonne prof. Pour un cours où elle doit faire attention à ce qu'elle dit par peur de la haine. Elle a fait un superbe travail et je la reprendrai sans hésiter. Genre et perspective en histoire est le cours en question. Donc vous voyez comment fragile le cours peu être. Quand même très bonne prof, bonne personalité et juste

Fantastic prof. Had her for "La France de l'ancien regime" a few years ago, hope she's still teaching. Engaging and entertaining lectures, gives good feedback, and is quite easy to communicate with. Really makes you interested in the subject and I left the course with a lot under my belt. Would 110% take a course with again.

She is hands down the funniest teacher Ive had so far! Really passionate about her subject so she makes the lectures SO interesting. The exams are quite easy because she gives you hint of what will be on them. Will definitely take a class with her again.

At first this class seems great, she gets you with her ''outgoing storytelling''. First midterm pretty easy. AND THEN bam there's the paper project that she even said herself you're lucky if you get a C+. The final exam is essay questions that you know in advance but still is hard because she is hard to please. Her expectations are too high sigh

J'ai adoré mon cours avec la prof Sylvie Perrier. Elle est toujours de bonne humeur et aime raconter des blagues. Elle est toujours disponible pour répondre aux questions lors de ses heures de bureau. L'examen de mi-session était facile et elle n'est pas trop stricte lors de la correction. Je reprendrai définitivement un cours avec elle!

She's a great professor, can't recommend her enough. I found her to be somewhat tough with grades but she gives good feedback and her expectations are clear. For immersion students she speaks very clearly and her lectures are very fun and easy to follow.
Prof Perrier is an amazing prof that keeps students engaged. She explains things clearly (enough for Immersion students to understand)! Definitely try and get her as a prof if you can.

Such a great prof, really helpful, and her lectures are really clear. She's very accommodating to french immersion students and the way she lectures makes it fairly easy to understand for those who have french as a second language. One of the best history profs at ottawa by far!

She's a great prof who is very passionate about  what she teaches. There's only one midterm which was a piece of cake but she gives you two papers which are decently difficult. The final was open-book with 2 essay questions. All in all she's a great prof and I would definitely take her class again :)

Great prof. Funny and smart.  Her assignments are tough, and you get the grade you deserve. Her lectures are very interesting because she uses multiple visual sources (mostly art), which compliment the class very nicely. She's friendly and charismatic. Best history prof I've had so far.
Très, très bon cours!! Je le recommande fortement!! Les intras et l'examen final ne vous surprendrons pas et sont juste. Excellent prof!!

Super gentille et excellent cours. Bien organisée. Le petit livre/roman n'était pas super utile. Le midterm était facile (du parcoeurs), les rédactions un peu difficiles mais faisables (beaucoup de support était aussi offert par le TA), et l'examen un peu compliqué mais tout de même raisonnable et à livre ouvert. Fortement recommandé.

Great prof, very interesting lectures, the assignments are really annoying but doable (two 2-3 page essays about readings). Midterm is all by-heart but its really clear, final exam is open book but still complicated. Overall, really great and interesting! PS: only buy the course pack with the articles, the little novel is useless (never used it).
Excellente!! Elle rends les cours amusant et les travaux sont très bien expliqués. Elle est toujours disponible pour répondre aux questions. Meilleure professeure de l'université!!

Excellente enseignante et toujours disponible pour aider! Mais elle est sévère sur les compositions écrites, et les assistants sont presque impossible à satisfaire. Toutefois, c'est un excellent cours et j'ai beaucoup appris!

Really clear, fair prof. She is very helpful during office hours and is really encouraging towards the immersion students. She speaks slowly and repeats the important stuff so it's easier for everyone to mark down. The midterm was fairly simple but attendance is mandatory to do well. Overall a really good class.

If you can get this prof definitely take one of her classes. She is funny, easy to understand, and her lectures are really interesting. This class is also really good if you are in French Immersion, because the FLS teacher that she works with actually knows what is going on in Mme. Perrier's class.

OMG ! La meilleure professeure à vie à l'Université ! Elle devrait apprendre aux autres professeurs à enseigner ! Elle est juste trop bonne ! Wow ! Si vous voulez avoir du fun, prenez son cours !!!!!! One of the best teacher of OttawaU, she should teach the other teachers ! She's awesome ! If you want to have fun take her class!!!!
I LOVED LOVED this teacher! Would take one of her classes again in a heartbeat
crystal clear to understand, very funny and engaging way to teach the material which in itself i didnt find very interesting. very personable

She is a REALLY good teacher:I had her first year, first semester, and was extremely impressed (and relieved!)Ses attentes envers ses eleves sont claires, et les commentaires sur les tests sont tres constructives! Je n'dirai pas que le cours etait "facile", mais c'etait SUPER interressant, et j'ai appris bcp de choses!!!

Une des meilleure enseignante à l'univesité d'Ottawa. Elle devrait apprendre aux autres professeurs ses méthode d'enseignement! Elle est très terre à terre, Approchable, accadémiquement professionnelle
No Comments

Excellent prof. Makes every class interesting no matter what is being taught adding her own great sense of humour. Both written assignments as well as the final exam were explained in-depth and quite clearly weeks before. Marking is rather tough but still manageable if you put in some effort. Would no hesitate to take another class with her.

Mme Perrier est exellente!  Elle est toujours pleine d'énergie et elle rend ses lectures intéressantes.  Je m'ai jamais ennuyé dans ses classes.  Les travaux sont bien expliqués et l'examen est a livre ouvert, mais il faut quand même connaître très bien la matière.  Ces une exellente professeure!
It was okay I guess.
Amazing prof!
Very excellent prof.

Mme Perrier was fantastic! It was the only course I would be excited for at 8:30 am. I definitely recommend her, she makes history so much fun! She's extraordinarily helpful but marks a little tough, so work because the class is worth it!
She's an excellent prof. She's interesting, easy, and knows how to make it fun even at 8:30am.
An absolutely amazing professor! She is quite smart, knows her stuff well. She teaches in a way that makes it fun to learn. Has a great sense of humour, and uses it quite frequently when she teaches.

An absolutely amazing professor! Makes the subject material fun and is hilarious as well.  Take good notes - our exam was open book.  TA's were quite brutal for the projects, but she marks very forgivingly for the midterm!
Really good teacher! I really enjoy her class. Makes learning easy. A bit harsh in her comments on projects but very easy exams.
No Comments
Amazing. Really! Tough marker but always fair. She knows how to teach at any level (found one, at last) and cares about her students. Open to discussion, don't feel like you're an idiot. Just enjoy.
No Comments
No Comments
knowledgeable, esp. 4 1st yr. prof. needs a little work on her english vocab.
